{{short description|Speculative payment network and digital currency}}

'''Initiative Q''' is an attempt to create a new payment network and digital currency.<ref name="not crypto">{{cite web |deadurl=no |accessdate=22 November 2018 |url=https://www.vox.com/the-goods/2018/11/8/18075816/initiative-q-email-cryptocurrency-bitcoin-paypal-saar-wilf |archivedate=9 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181109000341/https://www.vox.com/the-goods/2018/11/8/18075816/initiative-q-email-cryptocurrency-bitcoin-paypal-saar-wilf |title=This new would-be currency isn’t crypto — but is it for real? |first=Nadra |last=Nittle |date=8 November 2018 |website=[[Vox.com]]}}</ref> It was created by [[State of Israel|Israel]]i [[entrepreneur]] Saar Wilf, who previously founded Fraud Sciences, a payment security company acquired by PayPal.<ref name="news.com.au"/><ref name="TiA">{{cite news |url=https://www.techinasia.com/talk/founder-challenge-visa-global-currency |first2=Orr |last2=Hirschauge |first1=Lilach |last1=Baumer |date=23 August 2018 |title=This serial founder wants to challenge Visa through a ‘global currency’ for the future |accessdate=31 October 2018 |work=[[TechInAsia.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2008/01/28/ebay-acquires-fraud-sciences-for-169-million/|title=eBay Acquires Fraud Sciences For $169 Million |work=[[TechCrunch]] |accessdate=8 November 2018|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="not crypto"/> Q is backed by [[Cato Institute]] [[economist]] [[Lawrence H. White]].<ref name="news.com.au"/> Unlike Bitcoin the scheme would not take measures to evade state regulation.<ref name="CUPMedia">{{cite web |language=Chinese |deadurl=no |website=cup.com.hk |publisher=CUP Media |url=http://www.cup.com.hk/2018/11/12/will-initiative-q-the-next-bitcoin/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122121712/http://www.cup.com.hk/2018/11/12/will-initiative-q-the-next-bitcoin/ |trans-title="Q coin" suddenly rises, is it the next Bitcoin? |title=Q 幣」突然冒起，是否下一個 Bitcoin？|date=12 November 2018 |accessdate=22 November 2018 |archivedate=22 November 2018}}</ref>

==Marketing==
The currency is marketed through [[chain email]] [[multi-level marketing]],<ref name="portfolio.hu">{{cite news |language=[[hungarian (language)|hungarian]] |title=Megőrül az internet az új fizetéses MLM-rendszerért - Kamu lenne? |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031110948/https://www.portfolio.hu/vallalatok/it/megorul-az-internet-az-uj-fizeteses-mlm-rendszerert-kamu-lenne.302726.html |archivedate=31 October 2018 |url=https://www.portfolio.hu/vallalatok/it/megorul-az-internet-az-uj-fizeteses-mlm-rendszerert-kamu-lenne.302726.html |deadurl=no |trans-title=Will the Internet be crazy about a new MLM pay-per-view system - would it be Kamu? |first=Daniel |last=Huszák |date=31 October 2018 |website=[[Portfolio.hu]] |accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> and will not be released until a critical mass of adopters identify themselves.<ref name="TiA"/><ref>{{cite web |date=26 October 2018 |first=Jemima |url=https://ftalphaville.ft.com/2018/10/26/1540526405000/Initiative-Q--an-elementary-pyramid-scheme-with-grandiose-ideas/ |last=Kelly |accessdate=31 October 2018 | website=[[FT Alphaville]] |title=Initiative Q: an elementary pyramid scheme with grandiose ideas [Update]}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Vox.com]] reported that more than 2 Million people had signed-up in 180 countries.<ref name="not crypto"/>

==Criticism==
In October 2018, Frank Chung of [[news.com.au]] wrote that the marketing style could be "perceived as a [[scam]] or [[pyramid scheme]]".<ref name="news.com.au">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181030052631/https://www.news.com.au/finance/money/investing/what-is-initiative-q-payment-network-insists-its-not-a-pyramid-scheme/news-story/193102b9fbb5c35d6365f7f34226908f |archivedate=30 October 2018 |url=https://www.news.com.au/finance/money/investing/what-is-initiative-q-payment-network-insists-its-not-a-pyramid-scheme/news-story/193102b9fbb5c35d6365f7f34226908f |website=[[news.com.au]] |deadurl=no |title=What is Initiative Q? Payment network insists it’s not a 'pyramid scheme' |first=Frank |last=Chung |date=29 October 2018 |accessdate=1 November 2018}}</ref> and FINTECH Singapore and Daniel Huszák of [[portfolio.hu]] compared it to [[multi-level marketing]] without the fee.<ref name="portfolio.hu"/><ref name="Fintech">{{cite web |url=http://fintechnews.sg/25640/fintech/be-careful-new-currency-project-initiative-q-is-all-over-social-media-data-risk |website=[[FinTechNews.sg]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122115623/http://fintechnews.sg/25640/fintech/be-careful-new-currency-project-initiative-q-is-all-over-social-media-data-risk |title=Currency Project Initiative Q Is All Over Social Media– Be Careful, Your Data or Reputation are at Risk! |date=8 November 2018 |archivedate=22 November 2018 |accessdate=22 November 2018}}</ref> Owen Gough of [[Digital Spy]] wrote 
"Is Initiative Q real or fake? Short answer – we have absolutely no idea."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tech/news/a869483/what-is-initiative-q-bitcoin-real-fake-scam/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101235354/http://www.digitalspy.com/tech/news/a869483/what-is-initiative-q-bitcoin-real-fake-scam/ |website=[[DigitalSpy.com]] |deadurl=no |archivedate=1 November 2018 |title=What is Initiative Q: Is it the new bitcoin, or just one big fake scam? |first=Owen |last=Gough |date=2 November 2018 |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref>

Brendan Markey-Tower of [[Stuff.co.nz]] explained in November 2018 that the scheme wouldn't "make you fabulously wealthy. It is, nonetheless, an interesting idea".<ref name="stuff">{{cite web |title=Initiative Q is not the new Bitcoin, but here's why the idea has value |deadurl=no |archivedate=6 November 2018 |website=[[Stuff.co.nz]] |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/business/opinion-analysis/108380918/Initiative-Q-is-not-the-new-Bitcoin-but-heres-why-the-idea-has-value |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106135456/https://www.stuff.co.nz/business/opinion-analysis/108380918/Initiative-Q-is-not-the-new-Bitcoin-but-heres-why-the-idea-has-value |first=Brendan |last=Markey-Towler |accessdate=22 November 2018}}</ref>

Huszák enumerated potential problems with the scheme such as no clear crypto-currency security measures, unclear transaction/[[Foreign exchange market|exchange]] costs, and potential for [[market manipulation]] by the largest holders of currency.<ref name="portfolio.hu"/>

